HEADWORD: Zincite
<hw>Zinc"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>Native zinc oxide; a brittle, translucent mineral, of an orange-red
color; -- called also <altname>red zinc ore</altname>, and <altname>red
oxide of zinc</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

